This paper involves natural language processing and deep reinforcement learning, which are common topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with tracking and predicting popular discussion threads, which falls under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel deep reinforcement learning architecture, which could be relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
